        "title": "Query from Firebase dB",
        "body": "<p>I am new to Firebase and would like to know how to retrieve all the entries, given one specific value, like <strong>names<\/strong>. My db is like this:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>{\n  \"-L6wXAM4Yt6OeUx6kLM9\" : {\n    \"date\" : \"Tue Mar 06 14:17:53 GMT-04:00 2018\",\n    \"names\" : \"Raamon\"\n  },\n  \"-L6wXAM84ti-Ea0vzKfx\" : {\n    \"date\" : \"Tue Mar 06 14:17:53 GMT-04:00 2018\",\n    \"names\" : \"Anne\"\n  },\n  \"-L6whnSSZXHxdjPvGgKI\" : {\n    \"date\" : \"Tue Mar 06 15:08:41 GMT-04:00 2018\",\n    \"names\" : \"Anne\"\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>My rules:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>{\n  \"rules\": {\n    \".read\": \"auth == null\",\n    \".write\": \"auth == null\"\n  }\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Should i use the <strong>Query<\/strong> function? Or something else?<\/p>\n",
